#: src/mathlib.c:681
#, c-format
msgid "%s: benchmark=%d\n"
msgstr "%s: benchmark=%d\n"

#: src/mathlib.c:752
msgid "Mathlib Help"
msgstr "Mathlib pomoć"

#: src/mathlib.c:788
msgid "Mathlib Benchmark Help"
msgstr "Mathlib pomoć za mjerila performansi"

#: src/mathlib.c:790
msgid ""
"Jobs are forked and run in parallel by xnec2c, whereas threads are used by "
"the mathlib implementation to parallelize the linear algebra calculation of "
"one job.  For parallel algorithms you can reduce the number of threads in "
"use by the algorithm with the following environment variables:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS thread limit\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP thread limit\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL thread limit\n"
"\n"
"Each benchmark specifies a complexity to indicate approximately how long it "
"will take to run.  For example, O(N) means the time will scale with N and "
"O(N*J) means it will scale with N*J:\n"
"  * N is the number of mathlibs selected here:\n"
"      File->Mathlib Benchmarks->Selected Mathlibs\n"
"  * J is the number of jobs specified on the command line with -j (eg, -j "
"8)\n"
"\n"
"Higher complexity options run more benchmarks to provide additional "
"information about how you might optimize your xnec2c runtime.  The benchmark "
"menu options are as follows:  \n"
"\n"
"* Parallel (-j N): O(N/J) time: Benchmark each mathlib in parallel with the "
"number of jobs specified on the command line with -j.\n"
"\n"
"* Single Job (-j 1): O(N) time: Benchmark each mathlib with a single job "
"even if -j was specified on the command line. This is useful to find the "
"fastest interactive mathlib that is used when the frequency is changed in "
"the UI by changing a Frequency MHz +/- widget or (right-)clicking on the "
"frequency plot\n"
"\n"
"* Iterate -j N/=2: O(N*log2(J)) time: Benchmark each mathlib in parallel "
"initially with the number of jobs specified on the command line with -j, and "
"then reduce the number jobs by half for each subsequent iteration until only "
"one job remains.  This is useful to find a balance between the number of "
"parallel jobs specified by -j and the number of threads used by the linear "
"algebra library as modified by the environment variables listed above.\n"
"\n"
"* Iterate -j N-=2: O(N*J) time: Same as -j N/=2 above, but instead decrement "
"the number of jobs by 1.  This takes the longest to run.\n"
msgstr ""
"Taskovi se račvaju i izvode paralelno od strane xnec2c, dok niti koristi "
"implementacija mathlib za paralelizaciju izračuna linearne algebre jednog "
"taska.  Za paralelne algoritme možete smanjiti broj niti koje koristi "
"algoritam sljedećim varijablama okoline:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# Granica niti OpenBLAS\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Granica niti OpenMP\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Granica niti Intel MKL\n"
"\n"
"Svako mjerilo performansi specificira složenost koja ukazuje na otprilike "
"koliko dugo će trajati.  Na primjer, O(N) znači da će se vrijeme skalirati s "
"N, a O(N*J) znači da će se skalirati s N*J:\n"
"  * N je broj mathlib-ova odabranih ovdje:\n"
"      Datoteka->Mathlib mjerila->Odabrane mathlib biblioteke\n"
"  * J je broj taskova navedenih u komandnoj liniji s -j (npr. -j 8)\n"
"\n"
"Opcije veće složenosti izvode više mjerila performansi radi pružanja "
"dodatnih informacija o optimizaciji xnec2c.  Opcije menija mjerila "
"performansi su sljedeće:  \n"
"\n"
"* Paralelno (-j N): O(N/J) vremena: Mjerenje svake mathlib paralelno s "
"brojem taskova navedenim u komandnoj liniji s -j.\n"
"\n"
"* Jedan task (-j 1): O(N) vremena: Mjerenje svake mathlib s jednim taskom "
"čak i ako je -j navedeno u komandnoj liniji. Korisno za pronalaženje najbrže "
"interaktivne mathlib koja se koristi pri promjeni frekvencije u sučelju "
"widgetom Frekvencija MHz +/- ili (desnim) klikom na grafikon frekvencija\n"
"\n"
"* Iteracija -j N/=2: O(N*log2(J)) vremena: Mjerenje svake mathlib paralelno, "
"početno s brojem taskova navedenim s -j, a zatim smanjivanje broja taskova "
"na pola za svaku narednu iteraciju dok ne ostane jedan task.  Korisno za "
"pronalaženje ravnoteže između broja paralelnih taskova (-j) i broja niti "
"koje koristi biblioteka linearne algebre prema varijablama okoline.\n"
"\n"
"* Iteracija -j N-=2: O(N*J) vremena: Isto kao -j N/=2 gore, ali umjesto toga "
"smanjivanje broja taskova za 1.  Traje najduže.\n"

#: src/mathlib.c:839 src/mathlib.c:846 src/mathlib.c:852 src/mathlib.c:869
#: src/mathlib.c:874 src/mathlib.c:989
msgid "Mathlib Benchmark"
msgstr "Mathlib mjerila performansi"

#: src/mathlib.c:840
msgid "Benchmarks are disabled while optimization is activated."
msgstr "Mjerila performansi su onemogućena dok je optimizacija aktivirana."

#: src/mathlib.c:847
msgid "You must load a NEC2 input file before running benchmarks."
msgstr ""
"Morate učitati NEC2 ulaznu datoteku prije pokretanja mjerila performansi."

#: src/mathlib.c:853
msgid ""
"Choosing a benchmark other than \"Single Job\" has no effect unless -j is "
"specified on the command line."
msgstr ""
"Odabir mjerila performansi osim \"Jedan task\" nema efekta osim ako je -j "
"navedeno u komandnoj liniji."

#: src/mathlib.c:870
msgid "You must select at least one math library to benchmark"
msgstr ""
"Morate odabrati barem jednu matematičku biblioteku za mjerila performansi"

#: src/mathlib.c:875
#, c-format
msgid ""
"This will run a frequency loop benchmark for each detected linear algebra "
"library and then provide a summary.  It may take some time to complete "
"depending on how big and how many frequencies your NEC2 will use. Detailed "
"timing will be provided in the terminal.\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"* Only one Intel MKL library can be tested without restarting xnec2c, so "
"select which one you wish to benchmark before proceeding or it will choose "
"the first in the list and skip the rest.\n"
"\n"
"* Thread congestion will occur for multi-threaded libraries when using the -"
"j N option if there are not enough CPUs available to accommodate the forked "
"processes in combination with library threads.  Consider reducing the value "
"of -j N for benchmarking to find what library works best with a mix of "
"forking and threading; you can use `top` to monitor your CPU usageand if it "
"reaches 0%% idle then you might consider reducing -j N.\n"
"\n"
"You may wish to experiment setting these environment variables:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS thread limit\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP thread limit\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL thread limit\n"
"\n"
"Click OK to proceed, this dialog will close when complete."
msgstr ""
"Ovo će pokrenuti mjerilo performansi petlje frekvencija za svaku otkrivenu "
"biblioteku linearne algebre i zatim pružiti sažetak.  Može potrajati, ovisno "
"o veličini i broju frekvencija koje će vaš NEC2 koristiti. Detaljna mjerenja "
"vremena bit će prikazana u terminalu.\n"
"\n"
"Napomene:\n"
"* Samo jedna Intel MKL biblioteka može biti testirana bez ponovnog "
"pokretanja xnec2c, pa odaberite koju želite testirati prije nastavka ili će "
"biti odabrana prva u listi, a ostale preskočene.\n"
"\n"
"* Gušenje niti pojavit će se za višenitne biblioteke pri korištenju opcije -"
"j N ako nema dovoljno CPU-a za forkovane procese u kombinaciji s nitima "
"biblioteke.  Razmislite o smanjivanju vrijednosti -j N za mjerila kako biste "
"pronašli koja biblioteka radi najbolje; možete koristiti `top` za praćenje "
"korištenja CPU-a i ako dosegne 0%% mirovanja, razmislite o smanjivanju -j "
"N.\n"
"\n"
"Možete eksperimentirati s postavljanjem ovih varijabli okoline:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# Granica niti OpenBLAS\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Granica niti OpenMP\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Granica niti Intel MKL\n"
"\n"
"Kliknite OK za nastavak, ovaj dijalog će se zatvoriti po završetku."

